# Chat socket conventions

## Placement

- **Low-level client** (connection factory, shared config): `src/shared/lib/socket.ts`.
- **Chat-specific** subscribe/unsubscribe, event handlers, mapping socket payloads: `src/features/chat/socket/` only.

## Standard events

Use these names for real-time chat (align client/server):

| Event | Direction / meaning |
|-------|---------------------|
| `message:new` | Incoming new message |
| `message:send` | Outgoing send payload |
| `typing:start` | Typing indicator on |
| `typing:stop` | Typing indicator off |

## Example

```ts
// BAD — constructing WebSocket URL in a random component
new WebSocket(url);

// GOOD — shared/lib/socket.ts exports createSocketClient(options)
// GOOD — features/chat/socket/chatSocket.handlers.ts registers handlers via that client
```

Do not import `features/chat/socket` from `shared/`.
